<br>
But yeah, you should work on your typing.  Numbers instead of letters is a really bad habbit, and won't help you get an artist for your ideas.<br>
<br>
Also, I'm not entirely clear on how the father dies.  His hand is grazed by the arrow.  It is a poison arrow?<br>
<br>
If I might make a suggestion, a good way to open the scene would be to have the family at dinner, possibly entertaining a guest, and have someone telling the story about how father had bested the demon.  Would be a good way to introduce the history of the plot without resorting to the &quot;A long time ago, in a feudal era far away&quot; epilogue.  Also, would be a cool place to make some cultural observation (traditional foods, eating habits, etc.) to give the reader a solid impression of the setting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=avscards33>avscards33</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/6/03 1:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=105.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I like the idea.. how bout this?</span><hr size=1> Ok, I liked the idea of them having a guest over for dinner, so I thought, why not have the dad owe the dinner guest something for like saving him during the war, so he has him over for dinner. As the father tells the story of how he killed mr. evil way back when, this guy stands up, pulls off his hood, revealing the scars/tatoos/ other evil stuff, and sledgehammers the father through the wall, outside or something..  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#336699>- </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs>Polykarbon BBS</a><font color=#336699> - </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm40>Story Ideas</a> <font color=#336699> - </font><a href="http://www.polykarbon.com">Polykarbon: Manga & Photoshop</a><font color=#336699> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.246g<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></